The paper deals with terrain visibility graphs, a well-known graph class in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also provides several graph-theoretic and algorithmic results, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The practical applications of terrain visibility graphs in areas such as physics, geography, and medical sciences suggest that it could also belong to cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
